p: District Court First Judicial District of W. T.
To W.H. Barret and Isabella Barret

Wherein an application has been made by Chalres Gahres and Martha Gahres Guardians of Ella Dora Cravens a minor to Statue to the Rose Joseph. G Lewis Judge of the District Court First Judicial District of Washington Territory and an order apointed for a writ of Habeas Corpus. Considering the land W.H. Barret and Isabella Barret to appear and produce the body of Ella Dora Cravens and the minor Ella Dora Cravens should not be be returned to Charles Gahres and Martha Gahres.

Therefore in the name of the United States can and commanded to a blame the Joseph W. Revies Judge Court to be held in in the Court house in the county Walla Walla Court of Walla Walla and Territory of Washington on Monday September 1st 1873 at 11 oclock A.M. then and then to produce the body of the said Ella Dora Cravens and grant custody to said minor child in from the care and custody of appointed and for care in the proceedings and such further order Court or may be in selection
